# Spectra CPQ Visual Style

Use this visual style for all landing page sections and UI components.

## Brand style

The interface should look like a continuation of the Spectra CPQ presentation:
clean, light, technological, friendly, and presentation-like.

Avoid:
- generic SaaS templates;
- heavy corporate B2B visuals;
- random stock photos;
- dark, aggressive, overloaded interfaces.

## Typography

- Main font: SF Pro Display.
- Use large, expressive headings.
- Headings may use uppercase or semi-uppercase.
- Keep typography clean, minimal, and readable.
- Use tight but comfortable spacing in headings.

## Colors

Use the following core palette:

- Accent purple: #A183FA
- Background: #FFFFFF
- Main text: #3F3F3F
- Light card background: #F4F4F4 or #F7F7F7

Rules:
- Use #A183FA for primary CTA buttons, accent cards, badges, icons, and key visual elements.
- Use white text on purple backgrounds.
- Use #3F3F3F for primary text.
- Keep backgrounds mostly white or very light gray.

## Layout

- Use a lot of whitespace.
- Use large clean sections.
- Prefer calm grid-based layouts.
- Use soft cards with 16–24px border radius.
- Cards should have either a light gray background or a purple accent background.
- Use subtle shadows only when needed.
- Alternate white sections with purple accent sections when it helps structure the page.

## Components

Buttons:
- Primary buttons: purple background, white text, rounded corners.
- Secondary buttons: light background or transparent style with dark text.
- CTA text should be direct and action-oriented.

Cards:
- Rounded, soft, spacious.
- No hard borders unless necessary.
- Important cards can be purple with white text.
- Secondary cards should be light gray with dark text.

## Graphics

- Use 3D illustrations from the Spectra CPQ presentation when available:
  people, gears, documents, laptop, charts, interface elements.
- Do not use stock photos.
- If the correct illustration is not available, use a placeholder with a clear TODO comment.

## Overall feeling

The design should feel:
- modern;
- light;
- technological;
- structured;
- trustworthy;
- not too formal;
- not too playful.